==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pertinency
<hw>Per"ti*nen*cy</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>pertinence</ets>.
See <er>Pertinent</er>.]</ety> <def>The quality or state of being
pertinent; justness of relation to the subject or matter in hand;
fitness; appositeness; relevancy; suitableness.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The fitness and <qex>pertinency</qex> of the apostle's
discourse.</q> <rj><qau>Bentley.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pertinent</ent>⟦br⟧
